$ System.Decimal (struct)

An instance of `System.Decimal` represents a number with the following characteristics
  • A sign
  • A 96-bit integer number
  • A scaling factor by which the 96-bit number is divided. The scaling factor is 10ⁿ for `n` in 0 … 28.

`System.Decimal` is a *struct*, hence, it derives from → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/ValueType[`System.ValueType]`.

sa:

  → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/_integral-numeric-types

  The → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types[SQL Server data type] that is suited best to store a `Decimal` is `money`.
